Selective registration is an additional verification feature that can be customized by application developers during object registration. It has three possible modes: - "Disabled". All saved objects are considered as modified and registered for exchange. - "Modified". Only objects with changes in data are registered for exchange. - "According to XML rules". Only objects with changes in attributes are registered for exchange. The list of attributes is obtained from conversion rules.
